soc.message

Class SOCGameOptionGetInfos

  • java.lang.Object
    • soc.message.SOCMessage
      • soc.message.SOCGameOptionGetInfos
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, SOCMessageFromUnauthClient

    public class SOCGameOptionGetInfos
extends SOCMessage
implements SOCMessageFromUnauthClient
    This message from client asks the server about a list of game options, or is a general request about all changes to game options. Used during SOCGameOption synchronization when client wants localization or is a different version than the server. The server will respond with GAMEOPTIONINFO message(s), one per option keyname listed in this message.

    If the only "option" keyname sent is '-', server will send info on all options which are new or changed since the client's version. (this usage assumes client is older than server.) This is so clients can find out about options which were introduced in versions newer than the client's version, but which may be applicable to their version or all versions.

    A client looking for all such changes but also info about specific options can send OPTKEY_GET_ANY_CHANGES as part of its optionKeys list.

    In v2.0.00 and newer, clients can also request localized descriptions of all options if available, by including OPTKEY_GET_I18N_DESCS as the last option keyname in their list sent to the server. Check server version against SOCStringManager.VERSION_FOR_I18N. Server's response sequence may include a SOCLocalizedStrings(TYPE_GAMEOPT) with any unchanged but localized game options.

    The keyname list sent by a client asking for localization would be:

    • If older than server: "-", OPTKEY_GET_I18N_DESCS
    • If same version: only OPTKEY_GET_I18N_DESCS
    • If newer than server: Each newer option name, then OPTKEY_GET_I18N_DESCS
    This message type introduced in v1.1.07; check server version against SOCNewGameWithOptions.VERSION_FOR_NEWGAMEWITHOPTIONS before sending this message.

    Robot clients don't need to know about or handle this message type, because they don't create games.

    Since:
    1.1.07

    • Field Detail

      • OPTKEY_GET_I18N_DESCS

        public static final java.lang.String OPTKEY_GET_I18N_DESCS
        I18N option-description request token "?I18N" sent from client when its locale isn't en_US.

        If the list of game option keys from the client includes this item, the server should check the client's locale and send localized descriptions for all game options available at this client's version.

        When present, this will be at the end of the list of option keys sent over the network, but isn't part of the optionKeys list. The receiving parser will remove it from the list and set hasTokenGetI18nDescs and/or hasOnlyTokenI18n.

        If the server does not have game option names in the client's locale, this token is ignored and only the changed options will be sent by version as described above.

        Introduced in v2.0.00: Before sending, check the server's version against SOCStringManager.VERSION_FOR_I18N.

        Since:
        2.0.00
        See Also:
        hasTokenGetI18nDescs, OPTKEY_GET_ANY_CHANGES, Constant Field Values

      • OPTKEY_GET_ANY_CHANGES

        public static final java.lang.String OPTKEY_GET_ANY_CHANGES
        Request token sent from client to a newer server to get info on any new or changed options when client also needs to ask status of some specific options.

        v2.4.50 was the first version with that requirement, because that version adds SOCGameOption.FLAG_3RD_PARTY. Earlier client versions would ask older servers about specific options, or ask newer servers about any new/changed options in general, never needing both of those sets of info at once.

        Since:
        2.4.50
        See Also:
        OPTKEY_GET_I18N_DESCS, Constant Field Values

      • optionKeys

        public final java.util.List<java.lang.String> optionKeys
        List of specific game option keynames to ask about, or null. Does not include OPTKEY_GET_I18N_DESCS, use hasTokenGetI18nDescs instead. At sending client, does include OPTKEY_GET_ANY_CHANGES if needed; receiving server uses hasTokenGetAnyChanges instead.

        If null, then "-" was sent unless hasOnlyTokenI18n.

        Before v2.0.00 this was private field optkeys, with public getter getOptionKeys().

      • hasTokenGetI18nDescs

        public final boolean hasTokenGetI18nDescs
        True if client is also asking server for localized game option descriptions (v2.0.00 and newer); will send OPTKEY_GET_I18N_DESCS along with optionKeys.
        Since:
        2.0.00
        See Also:
        hasOnlyTokenI18n, hasTokenGetAnyChanges

      • hasOnlyTokenI18n

        public final boolean hasOnlyTokenI18n
        True if client is same version as server, and is asking only for OPTKEY_GET_I18N_DESCS; will send OPTKEY_GET_I18N_DESCS as the sole "option key": "?I18N", not "-,?I18N". optionKeys must be null.
        Since:
        2.0.00
        See Also:
        hasTokenGetI18nDescs

      • hasTokenGetAnyChanges

        public boolean hasTokenGetAnyChanges
        True if client sent OPTKEY_GET_ANY_CHANGES as part of optionKeys. During parsing at server, this flag was set and that token was removed from optionKeys.

        Because it's seldom used, unlike hasTokenGetI18nDescs, this flag isn't final or a constructor parameter.

        Since:
        2.4.50

        okeys - list of game option keynames (Strings), or null for "-". Do not include OPTKEY_GET_I18N_DESCS in this list; set withTokenI18nDescs true instead. Do include OPTKEY_GET_ANY_CHANGES if needed.
        withTokenI18nDescs - true if client is also asking server for localized game option descriptions (v2.0.00 and newer); will send OPTKEY_GET_I18N_DESCS along with okeys. Before sending this token, check the server's version against SOCStringManager.VERSION_FOR_I18N.

      • SOCGameOptionGetInfos

        public SOCGameOptionGetInfos(java.util.List<SOCGameOption> opts,
                             boolean withTokenI18nDescs)
        Create a GameOptionGetInfos Message, optionally with a list of SOCGameOptions to ask about.

        If client and server are same version, consider using the other constructor SOCGameOptionGetInfos(List, boolean, boolean) because this one doesn't set the hasOnlyTokenI18n flag.

        Parameters:
        opts - list of game options, or null for "-". Will build message using these options' keynames. Can include OPTKEY_GET_ANY_CHANGES if needed.

      • toString

        public java.lang.String toString()
        Description copied from class: SOCMessage
        Simple human-readable delimited representation, used for debug purposes: SOCPutPiece:game=test5|playerNumber=3|pieceType=0|coord=40a
        Could also be used by a SOCServer.recordGameEvent(String, SOCMessage) implementation.

        Within this representation, message parameters should be in same order used by SOCMessage.toCmd() and parseDataStr(..). Should be parseable by SOCMessage.parseMsgStr(String) which calls SOCMessage.stripAttribNames(String), which your class can override if needed.
